atmSuSystemSwOperStatus.name: atmSuSystemSwOperStatus
atmSuSystemSwOperStatus.description: This value indicates if tftp-write operation (for downloading software from an external host) is allowed by the agent.

atmSuSystemSwSwitchVersionsCmd.name: atmSuSystemSwSwitchVersionsCmd
atmSuSystemSwSwitchVersionsCmd.description: This command is used to switch beetween software versions stored in the flash. setting this value to active will reset the agent and re-activate it with the new version ( only if new version is valid). on get-request this value will be always notActive.

atmSuSystemHistoryAlrTable.name: atmSuSystemHistoryAlrTable
atmSuSystemHistoryAlrTable.description: buffer contain history buffer of agent alarms.

atmSuSystemHistoryAlrIndex.name: atmSuSystemHistoryAlrIndex
atmSuSystemHistoryAlrIndex.description: A unique number to identify an entry in the history alarm table.

atmSuSystemHistoryAlrIfIndex.name: atmSuSystemHistoryAlrIfIndex
atmSuSystemHistoryAlrIfIndex.description: This value indicates the port on which the alarms occured. configuration(system) alarms have port index equal to 0.

atmSuSystemHistoryAlrDescription.name: atmSuSystemHistoryAlrDescription
atmSuSystemHistoryAlrDescription.description: This attribute is a text description of the alarm. The alarm descipion include alarm code and alarm text.

atmSuSystemHistoryAlrStatus.name: atmSuSystemHistoryAlrStatus
atmSuSystemHistoryAlrStatus.description: This attribute indicates the status of the alarm.

atmSuSystemHistoryAlrOccurrenceTime.name: atmSuSystemHistoryAlrOccurrenceTime
atmSuSystemHistoryAlrOccurrenceTime.description: This value indicates the date and time of the occurrence of the event that caused this alarm. Date and time format: YYYY-MM-DD, HH:MM:SS

atmSuSystemHistoryAlrVpi.name: atmSuSystemHistoryAlrVpi
atmSuSystemHistoryAlrVpi.description: This value indicates the ATM VPI of the connection associated with the event that caused this alarm. When not applicable, value is 0

atmSuSystemHistoryAlrVci.name: atmSuSystemHistoryAlrVci
atmSuSystemHistoryAlrVci.description: This value indicates the ATM VCI of the connection associated with with the event that caused this alarm. When not applicable, value is 0

atmSuSystemClearHistoryAlrListCmd.name: atmSuSystemClearHistoryAlrListCmd
atmSuSystemClearHistoryAlrListCmd.description: Setting this attribute to ON, enforce a clear operation on the agent history event buffer . On reading, attribute will always get status 'off' .

atmSuSystemCurrentAlrTable.name: atmSuSystemCurrentAlrTable
atmSuSystemCurrentAlrTable.description: table which contains all alarms Currently active ( status ON ) in the agent.

atmSuSystemCurrentAlrIndex.name: atmSuSystemCurrentAlrIndex
atmSuSystemCurrentAlrIndex.description: A unique number to identify an entry in the Current alarms table.

atmSuSystemCurrentAlrIfIndex.name: atmSuSystemCurrentAlrIfIndex
atmSuSystemCurrentAlrIfIndex.description: This value indicates the port on which the alarms occured. configuration alarms have port index equal to 0.

atmSuSystemCurrentAlrDescription.name: atmSuSystemCurrentAlrDescription
atmSuSystemCurrentAlrDescription.description: This attribute is a text description of the alarm. The alarm descipion include alarm code and alarm text.

atmSuSystemILMICommunity.name: atmSuSystemILMICommunity
atmSuSystemILMICommunity.description: Community string for ILMI requests. 10 chars.

atmSuSystemTrapMaxManagers.name: atmSuSystemTrapMaxManagers
atmSuSystemTrapMaxManagers.description: The maximum number of managers that can be registered for receiving traps and sending requests.

atmSuSystemAalSelection.name: atmSuSystemAalSelection
atmSuSystemAalSelection.description: Select ATM adaptation layers AAL1 or AAL2 Applicable for LA-140

atmSuSystemCodingLaw.name: atmSuSystemCodingLaw
atmSuSystemCodingLaw.description: This attribute indicates the Method/Law for decoding/encoding the voice information. aLaw (2) is the standard Law for E1 links. uLaw (3) is the standard Law for T1 links. Coding law is applicable for all the ports in the system

atmSuSystemISDNDataLinkActivation.name: atmSuSystemISDNDataLinkActivation
atmSuSystemISDNDataLinkActivation.description: This attribute indicates data link aactivation for all ISDN ports in the system. nonPermanent (2) = non permanent data link activation permanent (3) = permanent data link activation

atmSuSystemJitterBuffer.name: atmSuSystemJitterBuffer
atmSuSystemJitterBuffer.description: The field is set in ms and sets the jitter buffer size. The jitter buffer adapts the size of the LA140 traffic to the cdv (cell delay variation) of the ATM network.

atmSuSystemOperMode.name: atmSuSystemOperMode
atmSuSystemOperMode.description: The field indicates device mode of operation: ima (2) = Inverse Multiplex ATM - ATM traffic is distributed between links in IMA group. miniDSLAM (3) => each link serves as separate ATM interface.

atmSuSystemDSPGain.name: atmSuSystemDSPGain
atmSuSystemDSPGain.description: This object indicates DSP Gain. Range of possible values is -12....12. For LA-110 suset of this range is supported.

atmSuPortDataCnfgTable.name: atmSuPortDataCnfgTable
atmSuPortDataCnfgTable.description: Data Port global configuration table. this table include parametes which are common to the physical port and not depend on whether the port interface is Frame-Relay or ATM-DXI.

atmSuPortDataCnfgEntry.name: atmSuPortDataCnfgEntry
atmSuPortDataCnfgEntry.description: the entries at this table describes the configuration of the Data-Port.

atmSuPortDataApplication.name: atmSuPortDataApplication
atmSuPortDataApplication.description: This attribute indicates the protocol application which runs above the physical port.

atmSuPortDataRate.name: atmSuPortDataRate
atmSuPortDataRate.description: This attribute indicates the operation rate of the port. AmcdT1 / Ace-20T allowes rates up to 1536KBps ( options 1-12 ), while AmcdE1 / Ace-20E allowes all options.

atmSuPortDataDCD.name: atmSuPortDataDCD
atmSuPortDataDCD.description: This attribute define behavior of control signals DCD and RTS These signals may obey or ignore signal from remote device. The terms 'I signal' and 'C signal' are used when physical data interface is X.21 ; RTS = C signal, DCD = I signal

atmSuPortDataMode.name: atmSuPortDataMode
atmSuPortDataMode.description: This attribute indicates the port mode of sampling data physical.

atmSuPortDataCRC.name: atmSuPortDataCRC
atmSuPortDataCRC.description: This attribute indicates the type of CRC checking on receiving/transmiting frames.

atmSuPortDataClock.name: atmSuPortDataClock
atmSuPortDataClock.description: This attribute indicates the clock using for synchronization for the data port.

atmSuPortDataMaxNoOfConns.name: atmSuPortDataMaxNoOfConns
atmSuPortDataMaxNoOfConns.description: this object indicates the maximum number of cross-connect connections allowed beetween the ATM port and the Data Port identified by IfIndex.

atmSuPortDataConfNoOfConns.name: atmSuPortDataConfNoOfConns
atmSuPortDataConfNoOfConns.description: this object indicates the configured number of cross-connect connections exist beetween the ATM port and the Data Port identified by IfIndex.

atmSuPortDataIdleCode.name: atmSuPortDataIdleCode
atmSuPortDataIdleCode.description: This attribute is applicable only for application aal1Stream. It indicates the value to be transmitted whenever the port is idle.

atmSuPortDataClkPolarity.name: atmSuPortDataClkPolarity
atmSuPortDataClkPolarity.description: This object indicates the clock polarity. For LA-110/140 this object will be applicable only for X.21/V.35/data port

atmSuPortDataCtsStatus.name: atmSuPortDataCtsStatus
atmSuPortDataCtsStatus.description: CTS status - the signal state received from ATM network (for the local DTE usage). LA110 receiving RTS down from remote DTE device via ATM network, will change CTS signal state to down (off) toward local DTE device

atmSuPortDataRtsStatus.name: atmSuPortDataRtsStatus
atmSuPortDataRtsStatus.description: RTS status - the signal state received from local DTE (to be forwarded to ATM network). LA110 receiving RTS down from the local DTE device will transmit all '1' to ATM (in order to carry the signaling to remote LA110), and forward it (RTS-down) to far end through ATM cell (pointer field).

atmSuPortDs1CnfgTable.name: atmSuPortDs1CnfgTable
atmSuPortDs1CnfgTable.description: This table include expansion configuration to the DS1 physical port.

atmSuPortDs1CnfgEntry.name: atmSuPortDs1CnfgEntry
atmSuPortDs1CnfgEntry.description: the entries at this table describes the configuration of the agent physical.

atmSuPortDs1CnfgRxSensitivity.name: atmSuPortDs1CnfgRxSensitivity
atmSuPortDs1CnfgRxSensitivity.description: This attribute is the rx line sensetivity parameter used only for T1/CSU and E1/LTU interfaces.

atmSuPortDs1CnfgLBO.name: atmSuPortDs1CnfgLBO
atmSuPortDs1CnfgLBO.description: This attribute is the line-Build-Out indicates sensitivity of the DS1 interface. The user can define if the agent will be CSU or DSU (for T1 only) by choosing the right option. On E1 interface this is done by hardware, so this parameter cannot be written.

atmSuPortDs1CnfgRestoreTime.name: atmSuPortDs1CnfgRestoreTime
atmSuPortDs1CnfgRestoreTime.description: Determines the time passing from the disappearance of the loss of synchronization condition (red alarm) to the restoration of normal service. The options 1secFast(2) and 10sec62411(3) for E1 interfaces are proprietary implementation of the T1 standard to the E1 interface.

atmSuPortDs1CnfgInbandMng.name: atmSuPortDs1CnfgInbandMng
atmSuPortDs1CnfgInbandMng.description: A unique number to identify type of inband management over the link. For LA-104 and IMXi4, only one port may be used for inband management

atmSuPortDs1CnfgDedicatedTs.name: atmSuPortDs1CnfgDedicatedTs
atmSuPortDs1CnfgDedicatedTs.description: A unique number to identify Dedicated Time Slot for inband management of the T1/E1 port. It is applicable only when atmSuPortDs1CnfgInbandMng selected is not off. 1..24 - Dedicated TS of T1 1..31 - Dedicated TS of E1 255 - notApplicable (for agents that do not support this feature) Other values are invalid.

atmSuPortDs1CbrCnfgTable.name: atmSuPortDs1CbrCnfgTable
atmSuPortDs1CbrCnfgTable.description: This table include expansion configuration to the DS1 physical port.

atmSuPortDs1CbrCnfgEntry.name: atmSuPortDs1CbrCnfgEntry
atmSuPortDs1CbrCnfgEntry.description: the entries at this table describes the configuration of the agent physical.

atmSuPortDs1CbrIdleCode.name: atmSuPortDs1CbrIdleCode
atmSuPortDs1CbrIdleCode.description: An Idle code which sent on unused time-slots at CBR port .

atmSuPortDs1CbrRxTimeSlots.name: atmSuPortDs1CbrRxTimeSlots
atmSuPortDs1CbrRxTimeSlots.description: This value indicates the time-slots used by the port for receiving. It uses 32 bits ( in 4 bytes octet string ) for E1 and low 24 bits for T1. each bit represents a time slot for receiving : time-slot 0 = bit 0 (LSB - most right bit in last byte), ... ... time-slot 31 = bit 31 (MSB - most left bit in first byte ). value '0' indicate unused time-slot and value '1' indicates used time-slot. note : time-slots '0' and '16' are used for signalling in E1 interface.

atmSuPortDs1CbrTxTimeSlots.name: atmSuPortDs1CbrTxTimeSlots
atmSuPortDs1CbrTxTimeSlots.description: This value indicates the time-slots used by the port for transmiting. It uses 32 bits for E1 and low 24 bits for T1. each bit represents a time slot for transmiting : time-slot 0 = bit 0 (LSB - most right bit in last byte), ... ... time-slot 31 = bit 31 (MSB - most left bit in first byte ). value '0' indicate unused time-slot and value '1' indicates used time-slot. note : time-slots '0' and '16' are used for signalling in E1 interface.

atmSuPortDs1CbrMaxNoOfConns.name: atmSuPortDs1CbrMaxNoOfConns
atmSuPortDs1CbrMaxNoOfConns.description: this object indicates the maximum number of cross-connect connections allowed beetween the ATM port and the CBR Port identified by IfIndex.

atmSuPortDs1CbrConfNoOfConns.name: atmSuPortDs1CbrConfNoOfConns
atmSuPortDs1CbrConfNoOfConns.description: this object indicates the configured number of cross-connect connections exist beetween the ATM port and the CBR Port identified by IfIndex.

atmSuPortDs1CbrSignallingSampleTime.name: atmSuPortDs1CbrSignallingSampleTime
atmSuPortDs1CbrSignallingSampleTime.description: determines how often the signalling of the DBCES connections are sampled and thier activity determined.

atmSuPortAtmCnfgTable.name: atmSuPortAtmCnfgTable
atmSuPortAtmCnfgTable.description: This table contains global configuration to the ATM port.

atmSuPortAtmCnfgEntry.name: atmSuPortAtmCnfgEntry
atmSuPortAtmCnfgEntry.description: This object contains information about agent ATM configuration.

atmSuPortAtmCnfgIdleCellCLP.name: atmSuPortAtmCnfgIdleCellCLP
atmSuPortAtmCnfgIdleCellCLP.description: Determines the clp bit value for transmition in empty time slots.

atmSuPortAtmCnfgScramble.name: atmSuPortAtmCnfgScramble
atmSuPortAtmCnfgScramble.description: Determined by the standards if the cell will be scrambled or not.

atmSuPortAtmSNMPVpi.name: atmSuPortAtmSNMPVpi
atmSuPortAtmSNMPVpi.description: The Vcc Vpi for SNMP requests.

atmSuPortAtmSNMPVci.name: atmSuPortAtmSNMPVci
atmSuPortAtmSNMPVci.description: The Vcc Vci for SNMP requests.

atmSuPortAtmSNMPStatus.name: atmSuPortAtmSNMPStatus
atmSuPortAtmSNMPStatus.description: value indicates if the SNMP Vcc is available for management.

atmSuPortAtmILMIStatus.name: atmSuPortAtmILMIStatus
atmSuPortAtmILMIStatus.description: Value indicates if agent should respond to ILMI requests from the Atm switch or forward it. note: when using Atm to Frame-Relay configuration this value should be active to support ILMI. when using Atm-AtmDxi configuration the ILMI requests should be moved forward to the DTE or may be answered by the DCE.

atmSuPortAtmSNMPIp.name: atmSuPortAtmSNMPIp
atmSuPortAtmSNMPIp.description: The interface IP address for SNMP requests.

atmSuPortAtmCnfgCDVOptimization.name: atmSuPortAtmCnfgCDVOptimization
atmSuPortAtmCnfgCDVOptimization.description: value indicates if optimization of CDV (Cell Delay Varation) is enbabled.

atmSuPortAtmCnfgShapingMode.name: atmSuPortAtmCnfgShapingMode
atmSuPortAtmCnfgShapingMode.description: ATM Shaping mode. Three possible values: SW Shaping. HW Shaping - APC with NCITS = 1. HW Shaping - APC with NCITS = 2 The difference between the two hardware modes is in the connection cell granularity and maximum bandwidth (BW): * For NCITS=1, the granularity is of one cell and the max. BW is the uplink BW, * For NCITS=2, the granularity is of every two cells and the max. BW is half of the uplink BW.

atmSuPortAtmSNMPTrafficDescrIndex.name: atmSuPortAtmSNMPTrafficDescrIndex
atmSuPortAtmSNMPTrafficDescrIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the atmTrafficDescrParamTable which applies to the transmit direction of the VCL.

atmSuPortAtmIfStatsTable.name: atmSuPortAtmIfStatsTable
atmSuPortAtmIfStatsTable.description: The table contains additional statistics information about the ATM interface.

atmSuPortAtmIfStatsEntry.name: atmSuPortAtmIfStatsEntry
atmSuPortAtmIfStatsEntry.description: An entry in the ATM Interface statistics table.

atmSuPortAtmRxClp0Cells.name: atmSuPortAtmRxClp0Cells
atmSuPortAtmRxClp0Cells.description: The number of cells received with correct HECs and CLP=0 and not misrouted

atmSuPortAtmRxClp1Cells.name: atmSuPortAtmRxClp1Cells
atmSuPortAtmRxClp1Cells.description: The number of cells received with correct HEC's and CLP=1 and not misrouted.

atmSuPortAtmRxEfciSetCells.name: atmSuPortAtmRxEfciSetCells
atmSuPortAtmRxEfciSetCells.description: The number of cells received with EFCI bit set by the Agent

atmSuPortAtmRxOamCells.name: atmSuPortAtmRxOamCells
atmSuPortAtmRxOamCells.description: The number of OAM cells received with correct HECs.

atmSuPortAtmTxClp0Cells.name: atmSuPortAtmTxClp0Cells
atmSuPortAtmTxClp0Cells.description: The number of cells transmitted with CLP=0.

atmSuPortAtmTxClp1Cells.name: atmSuPortAtmTxClp1Cells
atmSuPortAtmTxClp1Cells.description: The number of cells transmitted with CLP=1.

atmSuPortAtmTxEfciSetCells.name: atmSuPortAtmTxEfciSetCells
atmSuPortAtmTxEfciSetCells.description: The number of cells transmitted with EFCI bit set by the Agent

atmSuPortAtmTxOamCells.name: atmSuPortAtmTxOamCells
atmSuPortAtmTxOamCells.description: The number of transmitted OAM cells.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTable.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTable
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTable.description: The table contains additional information about the ATM Vcl end points.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsEntry.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsEntry
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsEntry.description: An entry in the ATM Vcl statistics table.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxCells.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxCells
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxCells.description: The total number of cells received with correct HEC's.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxClp0Cells.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxClp0Cells
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxClp0Cells.description: The number of cells received with correct HEC's and CLP=0.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxClp1Cells.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxClp1Cells
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxClp1Cells.description: The number of cells received with correct HEC's and CLP=1.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxDiscardsCells.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxDiscardsCells
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxDiscardsCells.description: The number of cells, in ingress direction, discarded due to policing violation.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxCells.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxCells
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxCells.description: The total number of cells transmitted.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxClp0Cells.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxClp0Cells
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxClp0Cells.description: The number of cells transmitted with CLP=0.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxClp1Cells.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxClp1Cells
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxClp1Cells.description: The number of cells transmitted with CLP=1.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxTotalAISCells.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxTotalAISCells
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxTotalAISCells.description: Total number of AIS cells received on the VC.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxTotalCCCells.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxTotalCCCells
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxTotalCCCells.description: Total number of Continuity Check cells that were received on the VC.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTotalSuccLoopbacks.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTotalSuccLoopbacks
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTotalSuccLoopbacks.description: Total number of loopbacks that were requested by the ACE20 and for which there was a response (not supported).

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTotalFailLoopbacks.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTotalFailLoopbacks
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTotalFailLoopbacks.description: Total number of loopbacks that were requested by the ACE20 and for which there was no response (not supported).

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxTotalRDICells.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxTotalRDICells
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxTotalRDICells.description: Total number of RDI cells received on a VC.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTotalLOCSeconds.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTotalLOCSeconds
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTotalLOCSeconds.description: Total number of seconds during which there was loss of continuity on the VC - no data and no continuity check cells were received on the VC whilst it was in 'sink' continuity check mode.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxTotalLoopbackReque.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxTotalLoopbackRequests
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxTotalLoopbackReque.description: Total number of loopback requests received by the ACE20 on a VC.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxTotalAISCells.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxTotalAISCells
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxTotalAISCells.description: Total number of AIS cells that were transmitted on a VC.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxTotalCCCells.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxTotalCCCells
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxTotalCCCells.description: Total number of continuity check cells that were transmitted on a VC (when there is no data cells and the connection is in 'source' continuity check mode).

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxTotalRDICells.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxTotalRDICells
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxTotalRDICells.description: Total number of RDI cells transmitted on a VC.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxTotalLoopbackRespo.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxTotalLoopbackResponses
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxTotalLoopbackRespo.description: Total number of loopback responses that were transmitted as a result of loopback requests received.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxTotalLoopbackReque.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxTotalLoopbackRequests
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsTxTotalLoopbackReque.description: Total number of loopback requests that were transmitted by the ACE20 on a VC.

atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxTotalLoopbackRespo.name: atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxTotalLoopbackResponses
atmSuPortAtmVclStatsRxTotalLoopbackRespo.description: Total number of loopback responses that were received as a result of loopback transmitted by the ACE20.

atmSuPortFrLportTable.name: atmSuPortFrLportTable
atmSuPortFrLportTable.description: The table Contains configuration parameters of the Frame-Relay port and has expansion to frLportTable in RFC1604 MIB.

atmSuPortFrLportEntry.name: atmSuPortFrLportEntry
atmSuPortFrLportEntry.description: An entry in the Frame Relay Logical Port Information table.

atmSuPortFrLportSNMPDlci.name: atmSuPortFrLportSNMPDlci
atmSuPortFrLportSNMPDlci.description: The SNMP Dlci of this entry.

atmSuPortFrLportSNMPStatus.name: atmSuPortFrLportSNMPStatus
atmSuPortFrLportSNMPStatus.description: value indicates if SNMP over FR is available for management.

atmSuPortFrLportVCSigProtocol.name: atmSuPortFrLportVCSigProtocol
atmSuPortFrLportVCSigProtocol.description: The value of this object identifies the Local In-Channel Signaling Protocol that is used for this frame relay UNI/NNI logical port.

atmSuPortFrLportVCSigProcedure.name: atmSuPortFrLportVCSigProcedure
atmSuPortFrLportVCSigProcedure.description: The value of this object identifies the Local In-Channel Signaling Procedure that is used for this UNI/NNI logical port. The UNI/NNI logical port can be performing user-to-network network-side and user-to-network user-side procedures or bidirectional procedures. this parameter gets value 'notApplicable when the VCSigProtocol is none

atmSuPortFrLportCLLM.name: atmSuPortFrLportCLLM
atmSuPortFrLportCLLM.description: indicate if the configuration is supporting CLLM ( Consolidated Link Layer Management ) .

atmSuPortFrLportSNMPIp.name: atmSuPortFrLportSNMPIp
atmSuPortFrLportSNMPIp.description: The interface IP address of this entry.

atmSuPortFrPvcEndptTable.name: atmSuPortFrPvcEndptTable
atmSuPortFrPvcEndptTable.description: The table contains additional information about the Frame Relay end point.

atmSuPortFrPvcEndptEntry.name: atmSuPortFrPvcEndptEntry
atmSuPortFrPvcEndptEntry.description: An entry for FR end-point statistics ( expansion to RFC 1604 ).

atmSuPortFrPvcEndptTxFECNs.name: atmSuPortFrPvcEndptTxFECNs
atmSuPortFrPvcEndptTxFECNs.description: number of frames transmited with FECN ( Forward Explicit Congestion Notification ).

atmSuPortFrPvcEndptTxBECNs.name: atmSuPortFrPvcEndptTxBECNs
atmSuPortFrPvcEndptTxBECNs.description: number of frames transmited with BECN ( Backward Explicit Congestion Notification ).

atmSuPortFrPvcEndptTxDEs.name: atmSuPortFrPvcEndptTxDEs
atmSuPortFrPvcEndptTxDEs.description: number of frames transmited with the DE ( Discarded Eligible ) bit set.

atmSuPortFrPvcEndptRxFECNs.name: atmSuPortFrPvcEndptRxFECNs
atmSuPortFrPvcEndptRxFECNs.description: number of frames received with FECN ( Forward Explicit Congestion Notification ).

atmSuPortFrPvcEndptRxBECNs.name: atmSuPortFrPvcEndptRxBECNs
atmSuPortFrPvcEndptRxBECNs.description: number of frames received with BECN ( Backward Explicit Congestion Notification ).

atmSuPortDxiConfTable.name: atmSuPortDxiConfTable
atmSuPortDxiConfTable.description: This table contains ATM-DXI managment address (DFA) ending at the local agent. only LMI managment supported for ATM-DXI.

atmSuPortDxiConfEntry.name: atmSuPortDxiConfEntry
atmSuPortDxiConfEntry.description: This object contains information about agent Dxi interface.

atmSuPortDxiPortMode.name: atmSuPortDxiPortMode
atmSuPortDxiPortMode.description: This object identifies the dxi mode being used by the atm dxi port.

atmSuPortDxiSigProtocol.name: atmSuPortDxiSigProtocol
atmSuPortDxiSigProtocol.description: This value indicates if we using LMI signalling protocol or not using any signalling .

atmSuPortDxiSigDfa.name: atmSuPortDxiSigDfa
atmSuPortDxiSigDfa.description: The Signalling Dfa address . the default LMI Dfa defined for LMI by the AtmForum is 0.

atmSuPortCmdTable.name: atmSuPortCmdTable
atmSuPortCmdTable.description: General commands to be done on agent's ports.

atmSuResetConnsStatsCmd.name: atmSuResetConnsStatsCmd
atmSuResetConnsStatsCmd.description: reset statistics of all cross connections attached to this port. set-request is allowed only on the DATA Ports . for get-request value is always 'off'

atmSuPortEtherTable.name: atmSuPortEtherTable
atmSuPortEtherTable.description: The table Contains configuration parameters of the Ethernet port.

atmSuPortEtherEntry.name: atmSuPortEtherEntry
atmSuPortEtherEntry.description: An entry in the Ethernet Port Information table.

atmSuPortEtherIP.name: atmSuPortEtherIP
atmSuPortEtherIP.description: The interface IP address for SNMP requests.

atmSuPortEtherMask.name: atmSuPortEtherMask
atmSuPortEtherMask.description: The interface IP address mask for SNMP requests.

atmSuPortEtherDefaultGateWayIp.name: atmSuPortEtherDefaultGateWayIp
atmSuPortEtherDefaultGateWayIp.description: The Ethernet bridge default gateway IP address.

atmSuPortEtherSNMPStatus.name: atmSuPortEtherSNMPStatus
atmSuPortEtherSNMPStatus.description: The value indicates if the SNMP of Ethernet bridge interface is available for management.

atmSuPortEtherFragmentation.name: atmSuPortEtherFragmentation
atmSuPortEtherFragmentation.description: Fragmentation. When application is not router value must be 'notApplicable'.

atmSuPortEtherRIPMode.name: atmSuPortEtherRIPMode
atmSuPortEtherRIPMode.description: RIP Mode. When application is not router value must be 'notApplicable'.

atmSuPortEtherBridgingMode.name: atmSuPortEtherBridgingMode

Sum of limits allocated to all connections must not exceed the total amount of available buffers. Whenever a connection exceeds it's buffer limit due to congestion or burst - traffic is discarded

atmCbrCnfgRxTimeSlots.name: atmCbrCnfgRxTimeSlots
atmCbrCnfgRxTimeSlots.description: This value indicates the time-slots used by this connection for receiving. It uses 32 bits for E1 and low 24 bits for T1. each bit represents a time slot for receiving : time-slot 0 = bit 0 (LSB - most right bit in last byte), ... ... time-slot 31 = bit 31 (MSB - most left bit in first byte ). value '0' indicate unused time-slot and value '1' indicates used time-slot. On set-request the user indicates the time-slot he needs for requested ATM-Vcc by putting '1' to the right bits. note : time-slots '0' and '16' are used for signalling in E1 interface. Currently not in use. Must be '0'.

atmCbrCnfgRxBytesPerCell.name: atmCbrCnfgRxBytesPerCell
atmCbrCnfgRxBytesPerCell.description: number of bytes to be receive in order per cell to low the delay.

atmCbrCnfgTxTimeSlots.name: atmCbrCnfgTxTimeSlots
atmCbrCnfgTxTimeSlots.description: This value indicates the time-slots used by this connection for receiving. It uses 32 bits for E1 and low 24 bits for T1. each bit represents a time slot for receiving : time-slot 0 = bit 0 (LSB - most right bit in last byte), ... ... time-slot 31 = bit 31 (MSB - most left bit in first byte ). value '0' indicate unused time-slot and value '1' indicates used time-slot. On set-request the user indicates the time-slot he needs for requested ATM-Vcc by putting '1' to the right bits. note : time-slots '0' and '16' are used for signalling in E1 interface. Currently not in use. Must be '0'.

atmCbrCnfgTxBytesPerCell.name: atmCbrCnfgTxBytesPerCell
atmCbrCnfgTxBytesPerCell.description: number of bytes to be transmit in order per cell to low the delay.

atmCbrCnfgParity.name: atmCbrCnfgParity
atmCbrCnfgParity.description: Controls the use of pointer parity when using the STRUCTURED or STRUCTURED WITH POINTER connection type. as defined by atmCbrCnfgService. ON - Pointer parity bit generation at the transmit side, and checking of parity bit for error detection at the receiving side enabled. Supported only for STRUCTURED or STRUCTURED WITH POINTER service. OFF - Pointer parity generation and checking disabled. Supported only for STRUCTURED or STRUCTURED WITH POINTER service. N/A - Not applicable. This is the only option when selecting UNSTRUCTURED or STRUCTURED WITHOUT POINTER.

atmCbrCnfgService.name: atmCbrCnfgService
atmCbrCnfgService.description: Define if DSx service is structured or unstructured. A structured(3) interface is some nx64Kbps. (n x DS0 = n Time Slots) An unstructured (2) interface is full DSx, x >0. (1.544Mbps, 2.048Mbps, 6.312Mbps, 44.736 Mbps, or 34.368 Mbps.) This objects selects the connection type also for AAL1 Stream for Data port. The available selections depend on the data rate selected. For the 64 kbps rate: STRUCTURED WITH POINTER = structure(4) Use of the structured service as defined in ATMF AF-VTOA-0078.000. STRUCTURED WITHOUT POINTER : same as above, but without using a pointer (the resulting cell structure is similar to that of the unstructured service cells). Default: STRUCTURED WITH POINTER structuredControlSignalsTransport -Pointer is used to transfer Data Control Signals through ATM network. For other rates: STRUCTURED : Use of structured service as defined in ATMF AF-VTOA-0078.000. UNSTRUCTURED : Use of unstructured service as defined in ATMF document AF-VTOA-0078.000.

atmEtherCnfgPPPEncapsulation.name: atmEtherCnfgPPPEncapsulation
atmEtherCnfgPPPEncapsulation.description: This object define the encapsulation type requested for the connection. rfc1483 - Multiprotocol Encapsulation over ATM Adaptation Layer 5 (no PPP) PPP VC Muxed - For VC Based Multiplexing, the carried network interconnect protocol is identified implicitly by the VC connecting the two ATM stations, i.e. each protocol must be carried over a separate VC. There is therefore no need to include explicit multiplexing information in the Payload of the AAL5 CPCS-PDU. This results in minimal bandwidth and processing overhead. PPP LLC Muxed - LLC (Low layer compatibility) Encapsulation is needed when several protocols are carried over the same VC. In order to allow the receiver to properly process the incoming AAL5 CPCS-PDU, the Payload Field must contain information necessary to identify the protocol of the routed or bridged PDU. In LLC Encapsulation this informationis encoded in an LLC header placed in front of the carried PDU.

atmEtherCnfgAllocatedBuffers.name: atmEtherCnfgAllocatedBuffers
atmEtherCnfgAllocatedBuffers.description: This object enables user to limit the amount of buffers used by the connection. The limit set by this object will give the effect of a virtual buffer pool per connection. The user can allocate between 10 to 217 buffers to every connection. By default the limit is 50 buffers. Sum of limits allocated to all connections must not exceed the total amount of available buffers. Whenever a connection exceeds it's buffer limit due to congestion or burst traffic is discarded
